    "headerDoc": "STEP 963 — Combinatorics: Design Theory and Extremal Set Theory\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-21\n\n  Five open problems in combinatorial design theory and extremal set theory:\n\n  A. EXISTENCE OF PROJECTIVE PLANES\n     For which orders q does a projective plane of order q exist?\n     Known: q = prime power. Known non-existence: q = 6 (Tarry 1900), q = 10 (Lam 1989).\n     STATUS: The prime power conjecture is OPEN.\n\n  B. HADAMARD CONJECTURE\n     A Hadamard matrix of order 4k exists for every positive integer k.\n     STATUS: OPEN. Known for all k ≤ 664 (exhaustive construction).\n\n  C. STEINER TRIPLE SYSTEMS\n    "
